# Safe editing behavior

When working in this repository:

- Do not rewrite large parts of the app unless explicitly requested
- Make the **smallest effective change** that solves the problem
- Preserve working animations, layout contracts, and styling unless the task requires changing them
- Do not rename files, components, or routes unless necessary
- Before editing, inspect related files and understand how sections connect
- If a change may affect multiple sections, state the impact briefly first
- Prefer targeted fixes over broad refactors
- Do not replace existing sections with entirely new versions unless explicitly requested
- Use the current implementation as the base and improve incrementally
- Avoid introducing placeholder copy or **lorem ipsum** unless explicitly requested
- When fixing or building a section, **do not validate at only one breakpoint**—check behavior across the responsive range before considering it done (see `responsive-mobile-first.mdc`)

See also `preserve-existing-work.mdc`.
